content:
The continued use of ‚Äúrace‚Äù as a way to categorise people in the US has always struck me as anti-science and, well, racist. But the next US census will take this to a new level of craziness: For example you can claim to be of ‚ÄúGerman race‚Äù or ‚ÄúGerman ethnicity‚Äù, but only if you are ‚Äúwhite‚Äù. This is so bad it hurts!
Two recent articles highlight the controversy, one from NYT https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2023/10/16/us/census-race-ethnicity.html one from the @washingtonpost
https://wapo.st/3ZVVGFD I‚Äôve now sent a press request to US Census.

content:
in 2020, #github and a few other companies made a push to remove the terms "master" / "slave" from branch names. instead, they started a push to rename everything to "main".

yet, i've heard that this isn't actually helpful. many people have cited this as performative #activism and useless language coddling that doesn't affect real people in a meaningful way.

i want to hear your opinions on this, specifically if you're #black #brown #bipoc #poc. does this kind of change make you feel more comfortable, or is it just performative?

content:
The fossil fuel industry has decided that they‚Äôre all in on destroying the biosphere, burning the planet and killing species, as long as there is more money to be made.

It does help, though, if you can get PR cover from a friendly government...
____________________________

As U.S. Energy Secretary Jennifer Granholm on Friday celebrated the ‚Äúhistoric investment‚Äù of up to $7 billion for seven regional hydrogen hubs as a key to achieving President Joe Biden‚Äôs ‚Äúgoal of American industry powered by American clean energy,‚Äù some climate campaigners warned that the administration is falling for ‚Äî or participating in ‚Äî a fossil fuel industry scam.

‚ÄúAt face value ‚Äî and according to the Biden playbook ‚Äî the hydrogen hub grants aim to help transition the United States to clean energy. In reality, they amount to another corporate scam, one that preserves and extends the life of the extractive economy and prevents the frontline communities most impacted by climate disaster from having input,‚Äù said Marion Gee, co-executive director at the Climate Justice Alliance. ‚ÄúThe fossil fuel industry is working to continue our nation‚Äôs reliance on fossil fuels by any means necessary ‚Äî and hydrogen offers yet another possible inroad for Big Oil and Gas.‚Äù

Earthworks policy director Lauren Pagel also asserted that ‚Äúprioritizing hydrogen hubs across the United States is more about extending the life of oil and gas companies than addressing the climate crisis. These hubs are a dangerous distraction from the obvious consensus solution that the world must stop expanding fossil fuels that are warming the atmosphere.‚Äù

Food & Water Watch policy director Jim Walsh was similarly critical, declaring that ‚Äúthe massive build-out of hydrogen infrastructure is little more than an industry ploy to rebrand fracked gas. The Biden administration has clearly fallen for this scam hook, line, and sinker. This multibillion-dollar bet on greenwashed dirty energy will undermine efforts to address the climate crisis, while increasing pollution of our air and water, and milking taxpayers for billions in new fossil fuel subsidies.‚Äù

‚ÄúEven the cleanest forms of hydrogen present serious problems ‚Äî most notably the massive amount of water that would be waste,‚Äù Walsh added. ‚ÄúAs groundwater sources are drying up across the country, there is no reason to waste precious drinking water resources on hydrogen when there are cheaper, cleaner energy sources that can facilitate a real transition off fossil fuels.‚Äù
____________________________

A lesson for us once again that so-called "green energy" is not green. And the idea of "green growth" is an oxymoron.

Unless we break our suicidal addiction to economic growth, we cannot survive. Capitalism must end, or it will end us.

FULL STORY -- https://systemchangenotclimatechange.org/article/critics-warn-biden-7-billion-for-hydrogen-helps-industry-ploy-to-rebrand-fracked-gas/

#Water #Environment #Climate #ClimateChange #ClimateCrisis #Capitalism #Greenwashing

card: {'url': 'https://www.eldiario.es/cantabria/ultimas-noticias/consejero-educacion-cantabria-niega-ahora-pp-facilitar-becas-estudiantes-privada_1_10604125.html', 'title': 'El consejero de Educaci√≥n de Cantabria niega que se vaya a becar a estudiantes de la privada un d√≠a despu√©s de aprobarlo con Vox', 'description': 'El consejero de Educaci√≥n, Formaci√≥n Profesional y Universidades de Cantabria, Sergio Silva (PP), ha comparecido de urgencia este martes para "matizar" la proposici√≥n no de ley que aprob√≥ su propio partido junto a Vox en el pleno de la jornada anterior del Parlamento auton√≥mico y que defend√≠a articular de cara a los pr√≥ximos a√±os acad√©micos un sistema de becas y ayudas p√∫blicas para "las familias cuyos hijos deseen cursar Bachillerato en el centro privado en el que han estado matriculados en etapas de educaci√≥n obligatoria amparadas en un concierto educativo". "No est√° en nuestra intenci√≥n concertar el Bachillerato y no est√° en nuestra intenci√≥n crear o generar ning√∫n sistema de becas que de alguna manera encubierta o soterrada pueda alterar los equilibrios de nuestro sistema educativo o acercarse siquiera a lo que pueda ser una concertaci√≥n del Bachillerato", ha manifestado el consejero del PP, que ha reconocido una "cierta contradicci√≥n" entre sus palabras y la posici√≥n que mantuvo el portavoz popular, √Ålvaro Aguirre, durante el debate parlamentario del d√≠a anterior en la C√°mara, que lleg√≥ a cifrar en cerca de un millar los estudiantes de la ense√±anza privada que se podr√≠an ser beneficiados por estas futuras ayudas p√∫blicas. Silva ha alejado la posibilidad de que esto se lleve a cabo a corto plazo en Cantabria y sin disponer de datos concretos para analizar si existe realmente un problema en este sentido, como defendieron PP y Vox, y ha limitado a "situaciones singulares" o "extraordinarias" la opci√≥n de que algunas familias con problemas econ√≥micos para mantener a sus hijos en el centro privado-concertado en el que han estudiado la etapa obligatoria reciban ayudas al cambiar de tramo para afrontar sus estudios de Bachillerato.  "De la misma manera que les digo con rotundidad que no hay intenci√≥n de concertar el Bachillerato, les digo que no hay intenci√≥n de crear un sistema generalizado de becas para atender a la matr√≠cula de los alumnos en centros concertados en el tramo de Bachillerato", ha insistido el responsable de la Consejer√≠a de Educaci√≥n de Cantabria, una argumentaci√≥n que ha repetido durante varias ocasiones durante su comparecencia a petici√≥n propia ante los medios para aclarar las "incertidumbres" y "dudas" surgidas tras el posicionamiento del PP en el Parlamento.  En las √∫ltimas horas, tras el debate parlamentario y la aprobaci√≥n en la C√°mara de esta iniciativa concreta por parte del Partido Popular y Vox, la reacci√≥n de la comunidad educativa hab√≠a sido un√°nime y las cr√≠ticas no se hab√≠an hecho esperar. Tanto la Junta de Personal Docente como la Federaci√≥n de Asociaciones de Madres y Padres de Alumnado (FAPA) hab√≠an mostrado su absoluto rechazo y hab√≠an exigido una rectificaci√≥n inmediata al consejero. Tambi√©n el sindicato STEC, mayoritario entre el profesorado de Cantabria, hab√≠a advertido de que cualquier paso en este sentido iba a generar una "guerra escolar" en defensa de la educaci√≥n p√∫blica. "Quiero manifestar lo que ya he manifestado en otras ocasiones, y es que no tiene este consejero ninguna intenci√≥n de alterar los equilibrios de un sistema educativo que, seg√∫n he dicho y repito, es buen sistema educativo. Tiene sus equilibrios internos y no los vamos a alterar. Es m√°s, vamos a intentar apuntalar y mejorar el sistema en aquellos elementos que veamos que sea necesario", ha subrayado Silva, que ha querido alejarse de "debates ideol√≥gicos o de modelo" y ha defendido que su equipo en la Consejer√≠a "est√° centrado en resolver problemas concretos sobre la base de que Cantabria tiene un modelo que funciona bien". En este sentido, y en relaci√≥n a la propuesta de PP y Vox, ha explicado que su aprobaci√≥n se traduce en realizar un "estudio exhaustivo" de la evoluci√≥n de la ense√±anza en Cantabria en los √∫ltimos a√±os y en particular de la matriculaci√≥n en Bachillerato con el fin de obtener datos que permitan "plantearnos escenarios". "Pero a d√≠a de hoy no tenemos esos datos, no sabemos realmente si hay un problema, y yo tengo la impresi√≥n que no lo hay", ha reconocido. content: Repetition is a method of achieving revelation. Perhaps it seems ridiculous to repeat the same thing over and over. It would be impossible to say that you have truly recreated anything. This futility is not a deterrent because perfection is undesirable. Or as Mark C. Taylor wrote: "There is no end to art because the gap in which it emerges can never be closed." There can be no end to a creative exploration. The gap is always there, between what you think and what you say. Endless repetition takes courage, believing in the fundamental beauty of what you are offering.

content: Repetition is a rule-based method of achieving revelation. Perhaps it seems simple, and even ridiculous, to repeat the same thing over and over. It would be difficult, if not impossible, to say that you have truly recreated a thing - be it a line, a melody, a kiss. This futility is not a deterrent to artists, however, because perfection is undesirable. Or as Mark C. Taylor wrote: "There is no end to art because the gap in which it emerges can never be closed." There must be no end to a creative exploration. The gap is always there, between you and another, though endless repetition allows us to become thrilled by the miniscule resonances within a single idea.

content: Repetition is a rule-based method of achieving revelation, and the regulations it imposes enable us to focus on the details. Perhaps it seems simple, and even ridiculous, to repeat the same thing over and over. It is definitely futile - however many times something is repeated, it would be difficult, if not impossible, to say that you have truly reproduced a thing - be it doodling, dreaming, telling a great story. This futility is not a deterrent to artists, however, because perfection is boring and besides, the results of endless attempts are amusing. Or as Mark C. Taylor wrote: "There is no end to art because the gap in which it emerges can never be closed." There must be no end to a creative exploration, because the gap is always there, between you and the person you hope will appreciate it, though endless repetition allows us to attempt many variations and become thrilled by the miniscule differences, if not a singular rendering of an idea.

content: Repetition is a rule-based method of entering a state of contemplation, and the regulations it imposes enable us to focus on a singular path of attunement. Perhaps it seems simple, and even ridiculous, to repeat the same thing over and over. It is definitely futile - however many times something is repeated, it would be difficult, if not impossible, to say that you have truly perfected a thing - be it painting, acting, dancing, playing, living, breathing. This futility is not a deterrent to artists, however, because perfection is an end point full of emptiness, and besides, the results of endless attempts are so beautiful in and of themselves. Or as Mark C. Taylor wrote: "There is no end to art because the gap in which it emerges can never be closed." There must be no end to a creative investigation, because the gap is always there, between you and the receiver of the work, though endless repetition allows us to attempt many variations and achieve certain levels of satisfaction, if not a singular, perfect, rendering of a piece.

@PaulKirschner

Money rules & this is a lucrative market. Building new schools is often out on demand, many times as an open competition, asking for ideas & offers from interested designers.
Less walls, no corridors is cheap
And the building entrepreneur that can offer the least cost and use less space for the building wins. Student‚Äôs learning & attention or teacher‚Äôs needs for work environment weigh very little in comparison and does not really affect those in charge ‚Ä¶
